        {/* Understanding OCD - Enhanced */}
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border-2 border-neutral-100 p-8 md:p-12 mb-16 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">Understanding OCD and Online Treatment</h2>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-white rounded-xl border border-green-100 p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
                <div class="w-1 h-6 bg-green-500 rounded-full"></div>
                Common OCD Subtypes Treated Online
              </h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                Online therapy effectively treats all major OCD subtypes:
              </p>
              <ul class="space-y-3">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">Contamination OCD:</strong> Fears of germs, illness, or environmental contaminants</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">Harm OCD:</strong> Intrusive thoughts about causing harm to oneself or others</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">Checking OCD:</strong> Excessive checking of locks, appliances, or safety concerns</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">Symmetry/Ordering:</strong> Need for things to be perfect, even, or "just right"</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-green-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">Pure-O:</strong> Primarily mental compulsions with intrusive thoughts</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-white rounded-xl border border-blue-100 p-6">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
                <div class="w-1 h-6 bg-blue-500 rounded-full"></div>
                Evidence-Based Treatment for OCD
              </h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
                The gold standard treatment for OCD is Exposure and Response Prevention (ERP):
              </p>
              <ul class="space-y-3">
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">Exposure:</strong> Gradually facing feared situations or triggers in a controlled way</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">Response Prevention:</strong> Resisting the urge to perform compulsive behaviors</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">CBT for OCD:</strong> Cognitive strategies to challenge OCD thoughts</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">ACT for OCD:</strong> Accepting intrusive thoughts without engaging with them</span>
                </li>
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-blue-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <span class="text-neutral-700"><strong class="text-neutral-900">Medication:</strong> SSRIs often used alongside therapy for moderate to severe OCD</span>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-primary-50 to-white rounded-xl border border-brand-primary-100 p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
              <Shield class="h-6 w-6 text-brand-primary-600" />
