            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-4 hover:shadow-md transition">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-brand-primary-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Real-World Exposures</h4>
                    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                      Conduct exposure exercises in your natural environment with therapist guidance
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-4 hover:shadow-md transition">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-brand-primary-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Between-Session Support</h4>
                    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                      Message therapist during difficult moments or when completing exposure homework
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-4 hover:shadow-md transition">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-brand-primary-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Accessibility</h4>
                    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                      Access specialized OCD therapists regardless of geographic location
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-4 hover:shadow-md transition">
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <CheckCircle class="h-5 w-5 text-brand-primary-600 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" />
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Lower Barrier</h4>
                    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                      Easier to start treatment when OCD makes leaving home challenging
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* FAQs - Enhanced */}
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl border-2 border-neutral-100 p-8 md:p-12 mb-16 shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-neutral-50 to-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Can online therapy effectively treat OCD?</h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
                Yes! Research shows that online ERP therapy is as effective as in-person treatment for OCD. Many people find online therapy particularly helpful because they can practice exposures in their natural environment with therapist support.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-neutral-50 to-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">How long does OCD treatment take?</h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
                ERP typically involves 12-20 sessions, though this varies based on OCD severity and individual progress. Many people see improvement within the first few weeks of consistent ERP practice. Long-term maintenance may be needed to prevent relapse.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-neutral-50 to-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Will exposure therapy make my OCD worse?</h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
                No. While exposure can be uncomfortable initially, it doesn't make OCD worse. A skilled therapist guides you through gradual exposures at a pace you can handle, starting with easier challenges and building up. The discomfort decreases as you practice.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-neutral-50 to-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Do I need medication for OCD?</h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
                Not necessarily. ERP therapy alone is highly effective for many people with OCD. However, moderate to severe OCD often benefits from combining therapy with SSRI medication. Your therapist or psychiatrist can help determine the best approach for you.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-neutral-50 to-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">What if I can't stop my compulsions?</h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
                This is normal and part of the OCD cycle. ERP helps you gradually build the ability to resist compulsions. You'll start with easier challenges and work your way up. Your therapist will teach you strategies to manage the urge to perform compulsions.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-neutral-50 to-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-6 hover:shadow-md transition">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">How do I find an OCD specialist online?</h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
                Look for platforms that allow you to filter for OCD specialization or ERP training. When matched with a therapist, ask about their experience treating OCD and training in exposure-based treatments. Most quality platforms will help you switch therapists if needed.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* CTA Section - Enhanced */}
        <div class="relative bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-primary-600 via-brand-primary-500 to-brand-secondary-600 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 text-white text-center overflow-hidden shadow-xl">
          {/* Background decoration */}
          <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden opacity-20">
            <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-64 h-64 bg-white rounded-full mix-blend-overlay filter blur-3xl"></div>
            <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-64 h-64 bg-white rounded-full mix-blend-overlay filter blur-3xl"></div>
          </div>

          <div class="relative z-10">
            <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Start OCD Treatment?</h2>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-xl mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto opacity-95 leading-relaxed">
              Take our personalized assessment to find the best OCD therapy platform matched to your specific symptoms and needs.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
              <a href="/tools/matchers/therapy-platform-matcher" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-white text-brand-primary-600 px-8 py-4 rounded-xl hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-all hover:scale-105 shadow-xl font-medium">
                <Search class="h-5 w-5" />
                Find Your Perfect Match
              </a>
              <a href="/tools/assessments/ocd-screening" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 border-2 border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:bg-opacity-10 px-8 py-4 rounded-xl transition-all hover:scale-105 font-medium">
